REQUIREMENTS
   - Docker Engine 17.06.0+
   - Docker Compose 1.14.0

INSTALLATION
   1. Install Docker & Docker Compose
      Reference: https://docs.docker.com/engine/installation/ https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/
   2. In the same location of this file, run "docker-compose up -d"
      If everything went well, you should see the following output:
      Creating 6381docker_postgres_1 ...
      Creating 6381docker_postgres_1 ... done
      Creating 6381docker_auth_1 ...
      Creating 6381docker_auth_1 ... done
      Creating 6381docker_api_1 ...
      Creating 6381docker_api_1 ... done
      Creating 6381docker_nginx_1 ...
      Creating 6381docker_nginx_1 ... done
      
CONFIGURATIONS
   - The server will be listening on port 3000 by default. This could be modified in nginx/nginx.conf.
   
